			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3586')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=8817&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pet+Filtering+%28My+request+to+VI%29"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Here is the letter I sent earlier today to VI(via eqfeedback@soe.sony.com). I'm not sure what other avenue I should broach. But this is a start, I suppose. I hope other necros join me in my petition. It's the little things that could make playing more enjoyable... here is the letter.<BR>--<BR>I know that every necromancer has a grief to air with Verant. We all want to feel more integral in raid situations. We all want to be consistent damage dealers. I'm sure you've heard it all before. Well, I'm not here to discuss that. I want to talk about one thing that I've been missing for the past two years: pet damage. I'm level 60 and I don't solo anymore (this letter really isn't for the soloers). I've had my share of it throughout the years. If not grouping or raiding, I duo with my monk. Even with him, I have to turn on my necro's damage filtering because I receive so much spam; the few lines of pet damage is interspersed in the 8 line blocks of monk damage. In a group, this condition obviously worsens. I don't even want to mention what raids are like (the few where I can use poor old Jober), trying to scan for those mere scraps of damage among the thousands of hits. Why is this important? Well, seeing pet damage is to a necro what seeing melee damage is to my monk. When I see the pet hits, I feel I'm contributing solidly to the battle. I enjoy it. My request isn't to do more damage, but to see the damage I do. Even if he doesn't quad for 50s with dual fs daggers anymore, he still hits, and I want to see it. In fact, all pet classes want to be able to see it. Here is the remedy: a pet filter. Pet On (all pet damage), Pet Self (only your own), Pet None (self-obvious). This is an easy fix which would appease a lot of the damage hungry pet classes out there. Especially with all the Alternate Advancement experience groups gathering these days, its a very opportune time for this fix. Thank you for your time,</P><P>Yvin 60 Necromancer<BR>Yvang 57 Monk<BR>Legacy of Steel <BR>--</P><P>EOF -- Thoughts?</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

